Parliament, Tuesday, 24 January 2023 – The Chairperson of the Portfolio Committee on Sports, Arts and Culture, Ms Beauty Dlulane, has learnt with shock of the passing of Mr Moeketsi Molelekoa, an International Association Football Federation (FIFA) referee.
	
	The committee sends its heartfelt condolences to the Molelekoa family and the entire football community. Ms Dlulane said: “We are shocked and saddened at this news. It is unfortunate that one of our top referees, who joined the FIFA panel of referees and assistants, is now no more. Many people do not realise the hard work that comes with getting onto FIFA’s books as an official.”
	
	“Mr Molelekoa was a dedicated official, whose elevation into being an assistant referee bears testimony to this. The committee sends its heartfelt condolences also to the FIFA panel of referees.”
	
	Mr Molelekoa passed away on the weekend.
	
	ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF THE PORTFOLIO COMMITTEE ON SPORT, ARTS AN CULTURE, MS BEAUTY DLULANE.
	
